ry.MustRegister(InspectionGauge, ImageCacheHitsTotal)\n\t})\n}\n```\n\n**Changes from original:**\n- Added `ImageCacheHitsTotal *prometheus.CounterVec` to the var block (line 18, new)\n- Added the `prometheus.NewCounterVec(...)` initialization inside `InitCommonMetrics()` (after `TimeToInspectImageGivenMiss`, before the `MustRegister` call)\n- Added `ImageCacheHitsTotal` to the `metrics2.Registry.MustRegister(...)` call\n\n### File 2: `pkg/image/cache.go`\n\nIncrement the counter on cache hit, using `imageReference` as the `image_ref` label value.\n\n```go\n\tif architectures, ok := c.imageRefsCache.Get(hash); ok && !skipCache {\n\t\tlog.V(3).Info(\"Cache hit\", \"architectures\", architectures, \"hash\", hash)\n\t\tmetrics.ImageCacheHitsTotal.With(prometheus.Labels{\"image_ref\": imageReference}).Inc()\n\t\tdefer utils.HistogramObserve(now, metrics.TimeToInspectImageGivenHit)\n\t\treturn architectures, nil\n\t}\n```\n\n**Change from original:** Added one line after the `log.V(3).Info(...)` call on line 52:\n```go\nmetrics.ImageCacheHitsTotal.With(prometheus.Labels{\"image_ref\": imageReference}).Inc()\n```\n\nThis also requires adding `\"github.com/prometheus/client_golang/prometheus\"` to the imports in `cache.go`. The full import block becomes:\n\n```go\nimport (\n\t\"context\"\n\t\"crypto/sha256\"\n\t\"encoding/hex\"\n\t\"time\"\n\n\t\"github.com/prometheus/client_golang/prometheus\"\n\n\t\"github.com/openshift/multiarch-tuning-operator/pkg/image/metrics\"\n\t\"github.com/openshift/multiarch-tuning-operator/pkg/utils\"\n\n\t\"github.com/hashicorp/golang-lru/v2/expirable\"\n\t\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/util/sets\"\n\n\tctrllog \"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/log\"\n)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Summary of all changes\n\n| File | Change |\n|---|---|\n| `pkg/image/metrics/common_metrics.go` | Declare `ImageCacheHitsTotal *prometheus.CounterVec`, initialize it as `prometheus.NewCounterVec` with label `image_ref`, register it via `MustRegister` |\n| `pkg/image/cache.go` | 